- "ZIP codes" are geographic regions used for mail delivery and other services;
- "Population" refers to the total number of people living in a ZIP code;
- "Median household income" is the middle value of all household incomes in a ZIP code;
- "Per capita income" is the average income per person;
- "Poverty count" is the number of people living below the poverty line;
- "Unemployment count" is the number of people without jobs;
- "Total businesses" is the number of companies operating in the ZIP code;
- "Total employees" is the number of people employed within the ZIP code.

